Business Brief -- Spiegel Inc.:
   Retailer Posts 64% Plunge
   In 4th-Quarter Net Income
Despite efforts to "motivate" Spiegel catalog customers,
the "longer-than-anticipated recession" kept them from
spending, Spiegel said.
   For 1991, Spiegel said its earnings plunged 73% to $16.9
million, or 33 cents a share, including a pretax charge of
$10.8 million, or 11 cents a share, from the Honeybee
closings. In 1990, the company earned $61.5 million, or $1.18
a share. Sales in 1991 fell to $1.97 billion from $1.99
billion.